    <stitle>HOOD, GRILLE, FENDERS AND BUMPER - 7000 - REMOVE AND INSTALL - SPLASH PANELS</stitle>
    <svcsection/>
    <svcproc svcproctype="remove" graphiccount="3">
        <title>SPLASH PANELS</title>
        <svcsubproc>
            <title>Splash Panel- Removal</title>
            <para>The splash panels (
                <hotlnk xrefid="f0900732">Figure 32, Item 5</hotlnk>) on the 7000 series minimize splash and mud,
                protecting vital engine systems from corrosion and malfunction.
            </para>
            <figure id="f0900730" figsize="col-wide">
                <graphic filename="../figg09/g0900730.webp" type="webp" scalefit="1" scalefitwidth="312px"
                         scalefitheight="288px"/>
                <caption>Figure 30. Splash Panel 7300 -7500 (Passenger Side Shown)</caption>
                <calloutgroup>
                    <callout1>1. FORWARD SPLASH PANEL MOUNTING BRACKET</callout1>
                    <callout1>2. REAR SPLASH PANEL MOUNTING BRACKET</callout1>
                    <callout1>3. SPLASH PANEL MOUNTING BRACKET BOLTS</callout1>
                    <callout1>4. LOCK NUTS</callout1>
                    <callout1>5. FRAME RAIL</callout1>
                    <callout1>6. SPLASH PANEL</callout1>
                </calloutgroup>
            </figure>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Tilt the hood assembly forward and locate the attachment bolts (
                    <hotlnk xrefid="f0900730">Figure 30, Item 3</hotlnk>) at the forward lower section of the splash
                    guard mounting bracket (
                    <hotlnk xrefid="f0900730">Figure 30, Item 1</hotlnk>).
                </para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Locate the rear splash panel mounting bracket (
                    <hotlnk xrefid="f0900730">Figure 30, Item 2</hotlnk>). Loosen and remove the mounting bolts and nuts
                    (
                    <hotlnk xrefid="f0900730">Figure 30, Item 3 and 4</hotlnk>) from the mounting bracket.
                </para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Lift the splash panel upward from the mounting bracket clips.</para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Remove the splash panel.</para>
            </step1>
            <figure id="f0900731" figsize="col-wide">
                <graphic filename="../figg09/g0900731.webp" type="webp" scalefit="1" scalefitwidth="280px"
                         scalefitheight="312px"/>
                <caption>Figure 31. Driver Side Splash Panel (7600 Series Shown)</caption>
                <calloutgroup>
                    <callout1>1. SPLASH PANEL MOUNTING SCREWS</callout1>
                    <callout1>2. HOOD</callout1>
                    <callout1>3. OPTIONAL HOOD HATCH</callout1>
                    <callout1>4. SPLASH PANEL</callout1>
                </calloutgroup>
            </figure>
            <figure id="f0900732" figsize="pg-wide">
                <graphic filename="../figg09/g0900732.webp" type="webp" scalefit="1" scalefitwidth="368px"
                         scalefitheight="328px"/>
                <caption>Figure 32. Splash Panels</caption>
                <calloutgroup>
                    <callout1>1. SPLASH PANEL LOWER MOUNTING BOLTS</callout1>
                    <callout1>2. 7600 FILLER PANEL</callout1>
                    <callout1>3. HEADLIGHT HOUSING</callout1>
                    <callout1>4. DIRECTIONAL SOCKET COVER</callout1>
                    <callout1>5. SPLASH PANEL</callout1>
                </calloutgroup>
            </figure>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">With the hood tilted locate the 2 driver side forward mounting bolts (
                    <hotlnk xrefid="f0900732">Figure 32, Item 1</hotlnk>) attaching the splash panel to the front hood
                    assembly.
                </para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Remove the bolts and lock washers.</para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Remove the (2) rear splash panel mounting bolts and lock washers located along the upper
                    edge of the splash panel.
                </para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Remove the splash panel assembly.</para>
            </step1>
        </svcsubproc>
        <svcsubproc>
            <title>Splash Panel - Install</title>
            <para>Beginning on the passenger side:</para>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Align the splash panel mounting bracket holes with the frame rail mounting holes and
                    insert the mounting bolts (
                    <hotlnk xrefid="f0900730">Figure 30, Item 3</hotlnk>) and lock washers.
                </para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Hand tighten only.</para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Align the rear mounting bracket and frame rail holes, insert the mounting bolts and lock
                    washers.
                </para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Hand tighten only.</para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Tighten the splash panel mounting bolts.</para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Install the splash panel on the mounting bracket clips.</para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Proceed to the driver side and align the driver side splash panel mounting holes with
                    the mounting holes in the fender.
                </para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Insert the (2) front splash panel mounting bolts and lock washers in the hood mounting
                    holes. Hand tighten to the hood assembly.
                </para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Position the 2 rear splash panel mounting holes in place on the hood and install the
                    mounting bolts and lock washers. Securing it to the hood assembly.
                </para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Torque the mounting bolts to 125 to 140 in-lbs (14 to 16 Nm).</para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Close hood and lock hood latches.</para>
            </step1>
        </svcsubproc>
    </svcproc>
